# Database Rules

## Migrations
- Never edit the database directly. All schema changes go through `prisma migrate dev`.
- Never run `prisma db push` in any environment — migrations only.
- Migration names should be descriptive: `prisma migrate dev --name add-featured-flag-to-cake`.

## Prisma Client
- The Prisma client is a singleton instantiated in `server/src/lib/prisma.ts`.
- Never instantiate `new PrismaClient()` anywhere else.

## Seed Data
- Seed data lives in `server/prisma/seed.ts`.
- Seeds must be idempotent: safe to run multiple times without duplicating data.
- Use `upsert` with a stable unique field (e.g. `name` for cakes) to ensure idempotency.
- Run seeds with `npm run db:seed` from the server directory.

## Schema Conventions
- All models use `cuid()` as the default ID strategy (`@id @default(cuid())`).
- All models include `createdAt DateTime @default(now())`.
- Models that are updated include `updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt`.
- Avoid nullable fields unless the data is genuinely optional.
